# ============================================================
# park.dlg  —  Comprehensive example scene
# One file = one scene/view (the park).
# Each [interaction] is a separate dialogue graph.
# ============================================================

# Scene-wide background defaults.
# Any character listed here gets this bg unless overridden locally.
@bg Akihiko   bgAkihiko
@bg Yukari    bgYukari
@bg Kenji     bgKenji

== Scene: Riverside Park ==

# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 4 — Three-way conversation, multiple characters
# The player stumbles into an argument between Yukari and Kenji.
# ============================================================

[interaction: yukari_kenji_argument | Yukari arguing with Kenji at the gate]

Kenji: Yukari, the east path is closed after sundown. I've said it twice.
Yukari: And I've told you - I left my bag on the bench. It will take thirty seconds.
Kenji: Rules are rules. Come back tomorrow.

# Player arrives
Akihiko: Hey, what's going on?
Yukari: Kenji won't let me through to get my bag.
Kenji: Akihiko, stay back. This doesn't concern you.

Akihiko: Can we work something out here?

[choice]
    > Vouch for Yukari     -> @vouch
    > Side with Kenji -> @side_kenji
    > Stay out of it      -> @stay_out

@vouch
Akihiko: C'mon, she's not going to cause any trouble.
Kenji: ...
Kenji: Fine. Two minutes. And you're coming with her.
Yukari: Thank you.
Yukari(bgYukariClose): ...Both of you.
[end]

@side_kenji
Akihiko: He's got a point, Yukari. Come back in the morning.
Yukari: Are you serious right now?
Yukari(bgYukariClose): Fine. Don't talk to me tonight.
[end]

@stay_out
Akihiko: Actually - yeah, none of my business. Carry on.
Kenji: Smart man.
Yukari: Unbelievable.
[end]
